[normal]3.
[normal]7
[normal]              
[normal]This picture is significant in itself, but more so in 
[normal]view 
[normal]of recent exploratory research undertaken 
[normal]by th
[normal]is submission’s 
[normal]author
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]on the 
[normal]media’s 
[normal]so-called ‘agenda-setting’ role
[normal] – 
[normal]where 
[normal]they 
[normal]possess the power to direct 
[normal]citizen 
[normal]attention to particular issues, 
[normal]via
[normal] the quantity of coverage. Th
[normal]eir
[normal] output 
[normal]influence
[normal]s
[normal] the extent to which citizens consider 
[normal]an 
[normal]issue 
[normal]a significant 
[normal]one 
[normal]facing the country
[normal] (
[normal]its 
[normal]‘
[normal]salience
[normal]’
[normal])
[normal]. The analysis
[normal] 
[normal]explored 
[normal]the period between 2000 and late 2007
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]before 
[normal]‘the economy’ began to dominate
[normal] political,
[normal] media and public agendas. 
[normal]Unlike Figure 3.1, i
[normal]t 
[normal]only 
[normal]tracked 
[normal]press 
[normal]stories where climate figured in 
[normal]headlines
[normal]. In addition, 
[normal]it 
[normal]differentiated between 
[normal]stories 
[normal]from 
[normal]the broadsheets, the mid-market ‘black tops’
[normal] (Mail/Express),
[normal] and the ‘red top’ tabloids
[normal], 
[normal]and 
[normal]enter
[normal]ed
[normal] them 
[normal]separately
[normal] in the model
[normal]. 
[normal]A 
[normal]number of political events 
[normal](such as 9/11 and Gulf War 2) 
[normal]also 
[normal]figured 
[normal]in the
[normal] assessment
[normal], to determine if they had an
[normal]y
[normal] 
[normal]role 
[normal]in distracting 
[normal]citizens 
[normal]from environmental issues. Finally, and uniquely, our analysis factor
[normal]ed
[normal] in the 
[normal]Figure 3
[normal].
[normal]2
[normal]’s 
[normal]documentaries. But
[normal], in
[normal] 
[normal]addit
[normal]i
[normal]on
[normal],
[normal] a 
[normal]separate
[normal] variable was entered for 
[normal]t
[normal]he 
[normal]‘
[normal]Great Global Warming Swindle’
[normal] documentary
